commit.message: Update changelog

Check CallbackReference#cbstruct for null when checking existing Reference

The CallbackReference is held in a WeahHashMap, where it might be
removed from when it becomes eligable for GC. For this there is a null
guard in place, but when the callback reference is explicitly closed,
the associated native structure is freed and "nulled", this case also
needs to be guarded.
Add documentation how the pre-build binaries for the native library are build

commit.message: Add workflow to build native libraries for mac OS / darwin on github
Run tests on mac OS M1
Add lib/native/dragonflybsd-x86-64.jar

Add support for DragonFly BSD x86_64

DragonFly BSD is currently x86_64 only, so don't bother with other
architectures at the moment.

The changes are based on the existing support for other BSDs.

Enhance 'native/Makefile' to include more paths for searching for X11
headers, because the X11 header paths are different on BSDs.  In
addition, add the 'X11INC' variable to allow user to specify extra paths
for X11 headers if really necessary.

Tested on DragonFly 6.5 with OpenJDK 17.0.8 and Ant 1.10.13.
Add Jetbrains Toolbox and update idea link in README.md
Fix free_callback JNI weak reference leak

commit.message:
Handle ELF binaries without section header table

The ELFAnalyser failed to analyse the java binary on Java 8 for armv7
synology NAS systems (DS115j, ...). The binary did not contain an ELF
section header table, which caused an IndexOutOfBoundsException.
Build native library for freebsd-aarch64
Add support for FreeBSD aarch64 (it's now a Tier 1 arch).
